Wow. I love this. Putting the Foundation in such a dilemma every time an object breaches containment is genius, especially by the same tool they rely on. You have to wonder what the success rate of their anti-memes are; there's bound to be at least one person who remembers what happened at Älveå, and they're not pleased at all. Hell, if the world after that isn't in a Broken Masquerade situation, I'd at least imagine there's some juicy material to write from it.







